<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Sorry to refer to UO, but need to use it as example.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarquin">Tarquin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:12 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Sorry to refer to UO, but need to use it as example.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=713" TARGET=_self>On Favoritism...</A> (Thorim)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I've read a lot of posts clamouring about 'favoritism' by GM's

<BR>&gt; in Everquest.
<P>&gt; While I certainly hope that we will never see any favoritism, it
<BR>&gt; is certainly possible that it could crop up, in which case we
<BR>&gt; definately need to deal with it.
<P>&gt; If you observe something that you feel was favoritism by any of
<BR>&gt; the guide staff, PLEASE contact the Senior Guide on your server
<BR>&gt; (that is Abashi on the PvP server), or one of the other Senior
<BR>&gt; Guides such as myself.
<P>&gt; Please provide a clear, reasoned report on what actions you
<BR>&gt; observed, when, and where, and the names of the people and staff
<BR>&gt; involved.
<P>&gt; Favortism is not, and will not, be condoned or allowed in
<BR>&gt; Everquest, that is one of our foremost precepts.
<P>&gt; Thorim
<BR>&gt; Senior Guide, Everquest
<P>Yes I very much agree here..problem in UO was......GM could abuse you and yet there was NOONE you could talk to.. I mean who were I gonna email? customer service? aint gonna waste $20 buck phoning em and being on hold for 10 minutes! (assholes hold u for that long..long distance..)...
<P>I just want to mention that for EQ there should be someone who can make sure that GM's are being proper
<P>I mean I understand that some1 can have a bad day and in everquest with pks its obvious...person will exert anger onto them or be in bad mood or such...but when that person is GM, there is not much a person can do....
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
